newsitem.title: USA: CBOT rice ends mixed, export sales data cited.
newsitem.headline: CBOT rice ends mixed, export sales data cited.

text.p: CBOT rice futures closed mixed with underlying support possibly coming from a strong number in Thursday's USDA weekly export sales report, traders said.
"The export sales were excellent but the bulk of it was the PL480 business so it isn't that big of a deal," a trader said.
USDA Thursday said U.S. rice exports during the week ended September 26 were at 76,200 tonnes, 22 percent above the previous week and 43 percent above the four-week average.
Traders also said there was an increase noted in the producer hedge selling in the September contract.
Rice futures volume was estimated at 350 contracts, down from 432 Wednesday, according to the CBOT.
Rice futures closed two cents per cwt lower to 2-1/2 higher, with November up 2-1/2 at $9.78 per cwt.
